{
  "text": "6.2. Completing a triangulated category with silting objects. The aim of this subsection is to prove the following theorem. Proof. Let M be a silting object of C. Then by [CITATION_1] Theorem 3.8 b) ], there exists a dg K-algebra A together with a triangle equivalence from per(A) to C taking A to M . Therefore",
